The average acceleration is the change in velocity divided by the time interval:

\[
a_{\text{avg}} = \frac{\Delta v}{\Delta t}
= \frac{0 \text{ m/s} - 3 \text{ m/s}}{3 \text{ s}}
= \frac{-3 \text{ m/s}}{3 \text{ s}}
= -1 \text{ m/s}^2
\]

So the bicycle’s average acceleration is \(-1\) m/s².

Answer: A

